def: Tending to corrupt; full of corruption. [Obs.] "Corruptfulbribes." Spenser.
Bearing niter; yielding, or containing, niter.
In the form of an eye; resembling an eye; as, an oculiformpebble.

To check, silence, or put down, with reproof; to restrain byexpression of disapprobation; to reprehend sharply and summarily; tochide; to reprove; to admonish.The proud he tamed, the penitent he cheered, Nor to rebuke the richoffender feared. Dryden.

A beautiful crystalline compound, SiC, consisting of carbon andsilicon in combination; carbon silicide. It is made by heating carbonand sand together in an electric furnace. The commercial article isdark-colored and iridescent. It is harder than emery, and is used asan abrasive.
The quality or state of being organic.
A colorless oily liquid, C4H3S.CH3, analogous to, andresembling, toluene; -- called also methyl thiophene.
